item.title: CVE-2018-14822|2024-08-05T09:38:14.039Z -- entes -- emg12
item.description: Entes EMG12 versions 2.57 and prior an information exposure through query strings vulnerability in the web interface has been identified, which may allow an attacker to impersonate a legitimate user and execute arbitrary code.

item.title: CVE-2018-14826|2024-08-05T09:38:13.899Z -- entes -- emg12
item.description: Entes EMG12 versions 2.57 and prior The application uses a web interface where it is possible for an attacker to bypass authentication with a specially crafted URL. This could allow for remote code execution.
